---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Cadinene Project | News | Takuya Asano"
  description="Cadinene is an ongoing project by Takuya Asano, exploring scent, time, and the fading contour of sound through piano and repetition."
  ogImage="https://asanotakuya.com/images/cadinene-project.jpg"
  ogUrl="https://asanotakuya.com/news/cadinene-project"
  ogType="article"
>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="container header-inner">
      <a href="/" class="site-title">Takuya Asano</a>
      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="/works">Works</a>
        <a href="/news">News</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <article class="news-post">
        <a href="/news" class="back-link fade-in">← Back to News</a>

        <header class="news-post-header fade-in">
          <p class="news-date">2026.04.27</p>
          <h1 class="news-post-title">Cadinene Project</h1>
        </header>

        <figure class="news-post-image fade-in">
          <img src="/images/cadinene-project.jpg" alt="Cadinene project image" />
        </figure>

        <div class="news-post-content fade-in">
          <p>Cadinene is an ongoing project by Takuya Asano.</p>

          <p>
            It begins with an interest in scent, time, and the way sound changes
            its contour as it fades.
          </p>

          <p>
            The project takes its name from cadinene, a fragrant compound found
            in hinoki and other woods. Rather than treating scent as an
            explanation, Cadinene uses it as a way to think about time,
            volatility, memory, and the movement of sound.
          </p>

          <p>
            Through piano, repetition, subtle processing, and quiet shifts in
            texture, the project explores how a sound appears, lingers, blurs,
            and disappears.
          </p>

          <p>
            Cadinene is currently developing across recordings, short studies,
            and related visual materials.
          </p>

          <p>Selected studies and related releases will be added gradually.</p>

          <hr class="section-divider" />

          <p lang="ja">
            Cadinene は、香り・時間・音の輪郭を手がかりに進めているプロジェクトです。
          </p>

          <p lang="ja">
            ヒノキなどに含まれる香気成分 cadinene から着想し、香りそのものを説明するのではなく、揮発、記憶、余韻、輪郭の変化を音楽の構造として捉えています。
          </p>

          <p lang="ja">
            ピアノ、反復、微細な音響処理を通して、音が現れ、留まり、滲み、消えていく時間を探っています。
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script is:inline>
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add("is-visible");
        }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.12 });

    document.querySelectorAll(".fade-in").forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
  </script>
  <style>
    .news-post {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    }

    .back-link:hover {
      opacity: 0.65;
    }

    .news-post-header {
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }

    .news-date {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    .news-post-title {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: "Cormorant Garamond", "Noto Serif JP", serif;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
      line-height: 1.12;
      font-weight: 400;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .news-post-image {
      margin: 0 0 48px;
    }

    .news-post-image img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 520px;
      height: auto;
      opacity: 0.93;
    }

    .news-post-content p {
      margin: 0 0 20px;
      font-family: "Cormorant Garamond", "Noto Serif JP", serif;
      font-size: 1.08rem;
      line-height: 1.72;
      letter-spacing: 0.008em;
      color: #333333;
    }

    .section-divider {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      margin: 48px 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .back-link {
        margin-bottom: 32px;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
      }

      .news-post-header {
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .news-post-image {
        margin-bottom: 36px;
      }

      .news-post-image img {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .news-post-content p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.68;
      }

      .section-divider {
        margin: 36px 0;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
